      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems including patch tests and single-element tests executed against analytical solutions; residual norms confirmed below solver tolerance thresholds across all three FEA implementations in the ensemble."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study required; achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study performed across three element density levels; Richardson extrapolation applied to construct stiffness QOI. Grid convergence index below 2% for all critical quantities, confirming discretization error is acceptably controlled."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver convergence confirmed with force and displacement residuals below 1e-6 for all load steps. Contact algorithm stability verified through load-step sensitivity analysis across the full compression-bending load range."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Simulation protocols documented in a standardized analysis plan reviewed by three independent analysts. Blind re-analysis by a second analyst produced results within 1.5% of primary analysis outputs, confirming low susceptibility to user-driven variability."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Physics representation must be adequate for the compression-bending loading regime; achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic titanium alloy constitutive model justified by sub-yield loading regime in ASTM F1717 protocol. Bone analog (UHMWPE block) modeled as isotropic elastic; contact at screw-block interface uses augmented Lagrangian formulation validated against frictionless and frictional limits."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material and geometric inputs must be traceable to measured values; achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy elastic modulus and Poisson ratio sourced from ASTM F136 coupon testing on production-lot material. UHMWPE block modulus characterized by uniaxial compression testing. Screw geometry digitized from micro-CT at 15 micron voxel resolution with dimensional verification against engineering drawings."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sample size and traceability must support statistical comparison; achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs tested across two independent laboratories using production-lot 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screws. Sample traceability maintained through lot documentation. Between-laboratory coefficient of variation for stiffness was 4.2%, confirming adequate reproducibility for model comparison."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios; achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single compression-bending load condition per ASTM F1717 protocol. Variation in offset distance and load angle not explored. This single-condition limitation reduces achieved level to 2, below the required level of 3. Accepted as residual gap given the prescriptive nature of the ASTM standard and the regulatory submission context."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA inputs must be equivalent to experimentally measured parameters; achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions in FEA replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry to within 0.1 mm. Applied displacement rate converted to quasi-static loading consistent with experimental protocol. Material properties in FEA sourced from same production-lot characterization used to select test specimens."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric must be defined and applied; achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load compared using mean absolute percentage error (MAPE) and Bland-Altman analysis. MAPE for stiffness: 6.3%; MAPE for yield load: 7.8%. All FEA predictions fall within 95% limits of agreement of experimental distribution, satisfying the pre-specified acceptance threshold of 15% MAPE."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QOIs must be directly relevant to the intended regulatory decision; achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load are the primary mechanical performance endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. These QOIs directly inform the regulatory substantial equivalence determination for the 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screw."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario must be sufficiently similar to the intended use context; achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities directly replicate the ASTM F1717 test configuration using the same screw geometry, material lot, and bone analog specified for regulatory submission. The validation population (N=11, two labs) covers the production variability envelope. Validation scenario fidelity to the regulatory submission context is high."
    }
  ],
